          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">
          DRC-M23 ceasefire agreement</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>Summary: The DRC and M23 have signed a provisional ceasefire agreement, with the possibility of a complete ceasefire by August 18.</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>The what:</strong> The Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) and the M23 rebel group signed a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-provisional-ceasefire-agreement" target="_blank">provisional ceasefire agreement</a> in Qatar, which requires both sides to halt hate propaganda and refrain from capturing land by force. They will implement the agreement by July 29, ahead of a complete ceasefire expected on August 18, which will align with the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-us-brokered-decree" target="_blank">US-brokered decree</a> between DRC and Rwanda.  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         <strong>The background:</strong> Decades of conflict escalated when M23 rebels seized the cities of Goma, Bukavu, and two airports in the mineral-rich DRC. The rebels demand the release of the captured ethnic <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-spotlight-h2-7-tutsi-fighters" target="_blank">Tutsi fighters</a>, and Congo has demanded the withdrawal of the M23 troops from the captured land. Analysts suggest that the M23 withdrawal will depend on the concessions of the DRC. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         <strong>The big picture:</strong> Although Rwanda denied backing the M23, it has agreed to lift the defensive measures in the eastern DRC. The agreement also grants the US permission to utilize the DRC‚Äôs mineral wealth, raising concerns over future exploitation.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
