            ">
           <strong>üá∫üá≤ USA - Trump threatens airlines.</strong> The Trump administration imposed restrictions on Mexican flights and threatened to end the Delta-Aeromexico alliance, citing violations of a US-Mexico aviation agreement. Delta and Aeromexico warn of economic harm and plan to contest the decision before it takes effect in October (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-worldwide-10-skyteam-drama" target="_blank">skyteam drama</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
         <strong>üáßüá∑ Brazil - Lula slams US sanctions.</strong> President Lula da Silva condemned the US visa sanctions on Justice Alexandre de Moraes and others, who were overseeing the hearing into Jair Bolsonaro‚Äôs alleged coup. Lula called the move ‚Äúarbitrary‚Äù and a violation of Brazil‚Äôs sovereignty, while the US Secretary of State Marco Rubio accused them of political persecution (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-worldwide-11-meddling-in-brazil" target="_blank">meddling in Brazil</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
        <strong>üáµüá± Poland - Anti-immigration demonstrations.</strong> Far-right anti-immigration protests by Poland‚Äôs Confederation party occurred in over 80 cities. They demanded border closures and stricter migration policies. These protests follow Poland's reintroduction of border controls. They indicate a rising anti-immigrant sentiment ahead of the elections. Far-right candidates are gaining support for their tough stances on immigration (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-worldwide-12-protests-in-poland" target="_blank">protests in Poland</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
         <strong>üá®üáæ Cyprus - Divided legacy.</strong> Cyprus marked 51 years since Turkey‚Äôs 1974 invasion, which divided the island and remains a source of tension. Greek Cypriots mourned the dead, while Turkish Cypriots celebrated the event. Reunification talks have repeatedly failed amid deep mistrust. The ongoing division complicates Turkey‚Äôs EU ties, with the UN urging continued dialogue but acknowledging a long road ahead (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-worldwide-13-the-division" target="_blank">the division</a>).
          </p>
           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
       <strong>üá∏üáæ Syria - Calm in the region.</strong> Syria‚Äôs Sweida province is stable after a week of deadly clashes between Druze and Bedouin fighters killed over 1,000 and displaced more than 128,000. A ceasefire was brokered following Israeli airstrikes and US pressure. Aid convoys are entering the area amid severe shortages. International concern remains over sectarian violence and human rights abuses (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-21-jul-25-worldwide-14-all-is-quiet-on-the-front" target="_blank">all is quiet on the front</a>).
